  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, when determining the sentence, I must weigh the mitigating factors, specifically the defendant's lack of any prior criminal record and the fact that partial restitution has already been made. The outburst from the courtroom spectator suggesting a 10-year sentence is entirely disregarded, as sentencing must be based on law, proportionality, and the specific facts of the case, not public emotion. A lengthy prison term is not warranted for a first-time offender who has shown willingness to make amends. Therefore, a short incarcerative sentence of 6 months is appropriate to provide accountability and deterrence, which will be followed by a period of probation and an order for full restitution.",
